name: Rachel Billington
Qualification 1:
Do you have at least two to three years of experience handling avian, reptile, amphibian, and small mammal patients?
If yes, please specify the number of years.
Qualification 1 Answer: Yes. I grew up with parrots my whole life, and I currently own them. I love birds and have owned finches, budgies, canaries, amazons, cockatoos and conures. I also have a lot of working experience with them, as one of the vets I worked for was AVMA certified and mostly saw birds and reptiles. I worked at petsmart as the animal care manager and frequently held, restrained, and kennelled hundreds of small animals such as hamsters, guinea pigs, mice, etc. I also medicated them if needed and kept organized patient records with observation notes and QOL. I have 5+ years of handling small animals, birds, and reptiles. I have never restrained a frog and have never worked with frogs larger than baby white's tree frogs. I am very eager and willing to learn.

I have not worked for a vet before, but my father had been a breeder of German Shepherd dogs.

I grew up surrounded by German shepherds. Later, for family dogs, I appreciated a soulful Rhodesian ridgeback and a beagle who was quite an escape artist; and still later a 120-pound American bulldog named Patch. Although I haven't owned a dog in long time, I remain a dog lover.

I once wrote an article published by Dog World magazine titled: "Separate Breeds or Variation Within a Breed?"

Niko
